5:
Damn...
They just aren't bitin' for me today.
How about you?
13:
Fishing poles?
Tsk, tsk. You two have SO much to learn.
18:
The hell are you goin' on about?
How're we supposed to fish without
fishing poles?
21: Easy. Here, watch and learn, guppies.
26:
Now pay attention, okay?
I'm only going to show you this once.
THIS is how you fish... Tatiana-style!
35: Well? Think you boys are up for it?
39:
I admit that was rather impressive,
but how do you plan on retrieving it?
42:
Isn't it obvious? Here, take a closer look
at the knife.
46:
Hmph, I should've guessed.
You've got a string around it.
49:
I guess that's why they call you the
Swiftblade, huh?
52:
Yeah, well...
That ain't fishing if you ask me.
57:
You've gotta be able to do at least this
much if you're gonna live here, right?
60:
Uh... We don't actually live around here,
but yeah. Do what you want.
64:
That's right. We live in Starview,
remember? But that was a really neat
trick!
67:
*sigh*
Isn't Starview Village just the best?
69:
All the food and drink you could ever
dream of... all for free!
71:
*sigh* Having friends sure is lovely,
isn't it?
74:
You're just planning on eating all our
food, aren't you?
78:
Speaking of which, it's almost noon!
We'd better get going.
83:
Sounds good to me! Let's crack open
some cold ones and enjoy this fresh
catch!
87:
It's almost ready, so hold on a little
longer.
91:
No worries! Just give me a bottle and
I'm a happy camper.
94:
Easy on the sauce, Tatiana.
You know how you get.
97:
Oh, don't be such a buzzkill, Nimbus.
I'm not THAT bad.
103: This... is some pretty damn good fish.
108:
Right? All the fish around there are,
really. I was hoping I'd get to pair it with
a quality bottle, but alas...
110:
You sure know your way around a fish
though, Alk! I might just have to loosen
my belt.
114:
There's still plenty left, so make sure
and eat your fill!
118:
Phew, I couldn't eat another bite!
Say, Alk, this would be the perfect time
for a digestif, don't you think?
121:
I don't think so. You're just gonna have
to deal.
128:
Actually, Tatiana... I'm actually about to
head back and do some more fishing.
131:
Do you think you could teach me how to
do that thing with your knife there?
134:
Interested in becoming a quickblader
yourself, are you? Fine by me.
137:
I mean, it's the least I can do after you've
spoiled me silly, right? But you'd better
do exactly as I say, got it?
142: Okay. I'll do whatever it takes!
147:
That's what I like to hear! So first,
I'm going to need you to get me a drink.
157:
Tell you whatif you manage to catch,
say, ten times as many fish as me, you
can have an aperitif before dinner.
Sound good?
162:
Deal! Nothing ventured, nothing gained,
right?
